        <abstract>
            <p>[Excerpt copied from a letter CD wrote to WHF.]</p> 
<p>CD’s gratefulness to William Buckland for his guidance on the glaciated terrain of N. Wales. "I am also convinced that the valleys of Glen Roy … have been occupied by arms of the Sea, &amp; very likely, (for on that point I cannot <hi rend="italic">of course</hi> doubt Agassiz &amp; Buckland) by glaciers also."</p> 
        </abstract>
